l%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Inflation%20Expectations%20In%20India%20May%20Stabilise%2C%20Edge%20Down%20Going%20Ahead%3A%20RBI%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EInflation%20expectations%20in%20India%20may%20stabilise%20and%20edge%20down%20going%20ahead%20but%20renewed%20pressures%20from%20cereals%20and%20proteins%20cannot%20be%20ruled%20out%2C%20the%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20India%20said%20in%20its%20February%20bulletin%20published%20on%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia's%20retail%20inflation%20eased%20to%20a%20three-month%20low%20of%205.1%25%20in%20January%2C%20from%205.69%25%20in%20December%20and%205.55%25%20in%20November.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOverall%20inflation%20developments%20are%20turning%20favourable%2C%20providing%20a%20stable%20environment%20for%20corporates%20to%20plan%20expansion%20strategies%20in%20anticipation%20of%20a%20pick-up%20in%20demand%2C%20the%20RBI%20wrote%20in%20its%20regular%20article%20titled%20'State%20of%20the%20Economy'.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCore%20inflation%20is%20at%20its%20lowest%20since%20October%202019%20and%20non-food%20wholesale%20price%20inflation%20remains%20in%20deflation.%20This%20should%20augur%20well%20for%20the%20input%20cost%20outlook%20and%20selling%20prices%20of%20manufacturing%20firms.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20RBI%20said%20evolving%20conditions%20are%20turning%20favourable%20on%20the%20agriculture%20front%20as%20well%20for%20the%20next%20financial%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20likelihood%20of%20the%20global%20economy%20exhibiting%20stronger-than-expected%20growth%20in%202024%20has%20brightened%20in%20recent%20months%2C%20with%20risks%20broadly%20balanced%2C%20the%20central%20bank%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Indian%20economy%20continues%20to%20sustain%20the%20momentum%20achieved%20in%20the%20first%20half%20of%202023-24%2C%20going%20by%20high-frequency%20indicators.%20Expectations%20of%20a%20fresh%20round%20of%20capex%20by%20the%20corporate%20sector%20are%20likely%20to%20fuel%20the%20next%20leg%20of%20growth.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20separate%20article%2C%20the%20RBI%20said%20internal%20simulations%20showed%20that%20the%20government's%20debt-to-GDP%20ratio%20would%20swerve%20below%20the%20projected%20path%20set%20out%20by%20the%20International%20Monetary%20Fund%20(IMF)%20in%20its%20latest%20Article%20IV%20consultation%20report%20for%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20recalibrating%20expenditures%2C%20India's%20debt-GDP%20ratio%20is%20projected%20to%20drop%20to%2073.4%25%20by%202030-31%2C%20around%205%20percentage%20points%20lower%20than%20the%20IMF's%20projected%20trajectory%20of%2078.2%25%2C%20the%20central%20bank%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20in%20this%20context%20that%20we%20reject%20the%20IMF's%20contention%20that%20if%20historical%20shocks%20materialise%2C%20India's%20general%20government%20debt%20would%20exceed%20100%25%20of%20GDP%20in%20the%20medium-term%20and%20hence%20further%20fiscal%20tightening%20is%20needed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708451400000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-02%2Fi315trfg_inflation_625x300_12_February_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fbusiness-news%2Finflation-expectations-in-india-may-stabilise-edge-down-going-ahead-rbi-5095923%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Inflation%20expectations%20in%20India%20may%20stabilise%20and%20edge%20down%20going%20ahead%20but%20renewed%20pressures%20from%20cereals%20and%20proteins%20cannot%20be%20ruled%20out%2C%20the%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20India%20said%20in%20its%20February%20bulletin%20published%20on%20Tuesday.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fbusiness-news%2Finflation-expectations-in-india-may-stabilise-edge-down-going-