0corporation%20on%20Tuesday%20(February%2020).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20comes%20after%20the%20bench%20headed%20by%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%20ruled%20that%20the%20election%E2%80%99s%20presiding%20officer%2C%20Anil%20Masih%2C%20made%20a%20deliberate%20attempt%20to%20deface%20eight%20ballots%20that%20were%20cast%20in%20favour%20of%20Kumar%20so%20that%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20Manoj%20Sonkar%20was%20declared%20the%20elected%20candidate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CYesterday%2C%20the%20presiding%20officer%20made%20a%20solemn%20statement%20before%20this%20court%20that%20he%20had%20done%20so%20as%20the%20eight%20ballots%20were%20defaced.%20It%20is%20evident%20that%20none%20of%20the%20ballots%20are%20defaced%20%5Bbefore%20Masih%20made%20markings%20on%20them%5D%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20bench%20said%20after%20it%20examined%20the%20defaced%20ballots.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20bench%2C%20the%20conduct%20of%20the%20presiding%20officer%20has%20to%20be%20deprecated%20at%20two%20levels.%20First%2C%20he%20has%20unlawfully%20altered%20the%20course%20of%20the%20mayoral%20election.%20Second%2C%20in%20making%20a%20solemn%20statement%20before%20the%20court%20on%20Monday%20(February%2019)%2C%20the%20presiding%20officer%20expressed%20falsehood%20for%20which%20he%20must%20be%20held%20accountable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFor%20the%20above%20reasons%2C%20we%20have%20come%20to%20the%20conclusion%20that%20the%20results%20declared%20by%20the%20presiding%20officer%20are%20unlawful%20and%20have%20to%20be%20set%20aside%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20court%20stated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurther%2C%20taking%20stern%20action%20against%20Masih%2C%20the%20bench%20ruled%20that%20a%20fit%20case%20is%20made%20out%20for%20the%20initiation%20of%20proceedings%20under%20Section%20340%20of%20the%20Code%20of%20Criminal%20Procedure%2C%20which%20deals%20with%20court-monitored%20inquiries%2C%20against%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CRegistrar%20Judicial%20is%20directed%20to%20issue%20a%20notice%20to%20Anil%20Masih%2C%20to%20show%20cause%20as%20to%20why%20steps%20should%20not%20be%20initiated%20against%20him%20under%20Section%20340%20CrPC%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20bench%20ruled.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMasih%20was%20also%20general%20secretary%20of%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20Chandigarh%20minority%20cell.%20After%20the%20controversy%20surrounding%20the%20mayoral%20election%2C%20he%20was%20taken%20down%20from%20the%20post%20on%20February%2012.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESC%20says%20no%20to%20fresh%20election%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAppearing%20on%20behalf%20of%20Masih%2C%20the%20solicitor%20general%20had%20sought%20fresh%20polls%2C%20which%20the%20BJP%20ideally%20wanted%20as%20it%20had%20already%20inducted%20three%20AAP%20councillors%20into%20its%20fold%20in%20order%20to%20muster%20enough%20numbers%20in%20the%20event%20of%20a%20re-poll.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20ruled%20against%20this%2C%20with%20the%20bench%20stating%20it%20was%20of%20the%20view%20that%20setting%20aside%20the%20entire%20election%20process%20is%20inappropriate%20as%20the%20only%20infirmity%20was%20found%20in%20the%20counting%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESetting%20aside%20the%20entire%20election%20process%20will%20compound%20the%20destruction%20of%20the%20democratic%20principles%20that%20occurred%20due%20to%20the%20conduct%20of%20the%20presiding%20officer%2C%20it%20stated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20bench%2C%20the%20court%20is%20duty%20bound%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20democratic%20process%20is%20not%20set%20at%20naught%20by%20such%20subterfuge.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20therefore%20of%20the%20view%20that%20the%20court%20must%20step%20in%20such%20exceptional%20circumstances%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20basic%20democratic%20mandate%20is%20ensured%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20bench%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECongress%2C%20AAP%20hail%20SC%20order%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20first%20reaction%20after%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20order%2C%20AAP%20supremo%20and%20Delhi%20chief%20minister%20Arvind%20Kejriwal%20thanked%20the%20court%20for%20saving%20democracy%20in%20these%20difficult%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKejriwal%20congratulated%20Kumar%20and%20said%20that%20he%20hails%20from%20a%20poor%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHis%20victory%20became%20possible%20because%20of%20the%20SC.%20This%20is%20a%20victory%20of%20Indian%20democracy%2C%E2%80%9D%20Kejriwal%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20statement%2C%20Congress%20president%20Mallikarjun%20Kharge%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20saved%20democracy%20from%20the%20fangs%20of%20an%20autocratic%20BJP%2C%20which%20resorted%20to%20dirty%20election%20manipulation.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20institutional%20sabotage%20in%20the%20Chandigarh%20mayor%20polls%20is%20only%20a%20tip%20of%20the%20iceberg%20in%20Modi-Shah%E2%80%99s%20devious%20conspiracy%20to%20trample%20democracy.%20All%20Indians%20must%20fight%20this%20onslaught%20on%20our%20constitution%2C%20collectively.%20Never%20forget.%20Our%20democracy%20shall%20be%20at%20the%20crossroads%20in%20the%202024%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections!%E2%80%9D%20he%20continued.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECongress%20leader%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20reacted%20by%20saying%20that%20Masih%20was%20just%20a%20pawn%20in%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20attempt%20to%20murder%20democracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBJP%20president%20J.P.%20Nadda%20had%20earlier%20said%20of%20Sonkar%E2%80%99s%20victory%20that%20it%20showed%20how%20the%20INDIA%20political%20bloc%2C%20of%20which%20both%20the%20Congress%20and%20AAP%20are%20part%20of%2C%20was%20not%20working%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThat%20the%20INDI%20Alliance%20fought%20their%20first%20electoral%20battle%20and%20still%20lost%20to%20%5Bthe%5D%20BJP%20shows%20that%20neither%20their%20arithmetic%20is%20working%20nor%20their%20chemistry%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FJPNadda%2Fstatus%2F1752241512560341137%5C%22%3ENadda%20said%20in%20a%20post%20on%20X%3C%2Fa%3E%20congratulating%20Sonkar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20Masih%20made%20the%20BJP%20candidate%20the%20winner%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20election%20for%20the%20post%20of%20mayor%20was%20conducted%20on%20January%2030.%20Two%20candidates%20were%20in%20the%20fray%20for%20the%20post.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKuldeep%20Kumar%20was%20a%20candidate%20set%20up%20in%20an%20alliance%20between%20the%20AAP%20and%20the%20Congress.%20The%20BJP%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20fielded%20Manoj%20Sonkar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThirty-five%20councillors%20as%20well%20as%20Chandigarh%E2%80%99s%20MP%20were%20eligible%20to%20vote%20during%20the%20mayoral%20election%2C%20taking%20the%20total%20number%20of%20eligible%20voters%20to%2036.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EElection%20to%20the%20post%20of%20mayor%20is%20governed%20by%20the%20Chandigarh%20Municipal%20Corporation%20(Procedure%20and%20Conduct%20of%20Business)%20Regulations%2C%201996%20and%20is%20held%20by%20secret%20ballot.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKumar%20was%20the%20favourite%20to%20win%2C%20since%20both%20the%20AAP%20and%20the%20Congress%20had%20total%20of%2020%20councillors%20(13%20of%20the%20AAP%20and%20seven%20of%20the%20Congress)%2C%20while%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20maximum%20strength%20was%2015%20votes%20including%20one%20vote%20from%20the%20Chandigarh%20BJP%20MP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Masih%20declared%20as%20many%20as%20eight%20votes%20of%20AAP%20and%20Congress%20councillors%20invalid%2C%20thereby%20declaring%20Sonkar%20as%20the%20new%20Chandigarh%20mayor%2C%20who%20won%20the%20election%20by%2016%20votes%20to%2012.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20case%20proceedings%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20prove%20beyond%20doubt%20that%20Masih%20had%20deliberately%20rigged%20eight%20opposition%20votes%20to%20favour%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20Sonkar%2C%20who%20has%20already%20resigned%20from%20the%20post%20on%20Sunday%20while%20apprehending%20stern%20action%20from%20apex%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20Masih%20had%20evidently%20marked%20the%20ballots%20for%20the%20purpose%20of%20treating%20them%20as%20invalid.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20doing%20so%2C%20he%20has%20acted%20beyond%20his%20remit%20of%20statutory%20regulations%2C%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20declaring%20Kumar%20as%20the%20new%20Chandigarh%20mayor%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20ruled%20that%20the%20ink%20marks%20placed%20by%20Masih%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20ballots%20have%20no%20consequence%20and%20that%20these%20votes%20would%20therefore%20be%20treated%20valid.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708428824000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F31224356%2FSupreme-Court-II-png.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fblow-to-bjp-as-supreme-court-declares-aap-candidate-winner-of-chandigarh-mayoral-poll%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20bench%20ordered%20an%20inquiry%20against%20Anil%20Masih%2C%20the%20election's%20presiding%20officer%20and%20a%20former%20general%20secretary%20of%20the%20BJP's%20Chandigarh%20minority%20cell%2C%20adding%20that%20he%20spoke%20falsehoods%20in%20his%20statements%20to%20the%20apex%20court.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A56%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fblow-to-bjp-as-supreme-court-declares-aap-candidate-winner-of-chandigarh-mayoral-poll%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Israeli%20Advance%20on%20Rafah%20Would%20Have%20%E2%80%98Dire%20Humanitarian%20Consequences%E2%80%99%3A%20Senior%20Gaza%20Official%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F20163806%2Fimage1170x530croppe.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAn%20extension%20of%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20military%20operation%20in%20Rafah%2C%20where%20over%20a%20million%20internally%20displaced%20Palestinians%20have%20been%20forced%20to%20shelter%2C%20will%20have%20%E2%80%9Cdire%20humanitarian%20consequences%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20UN%20Senior%20Humanitarian%20Coordinator%20for%20Gaza%2C%20Sigrid%20Kaag%2C%20said%20on%20Monday.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKaag%20reiterated%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.un.org%2Fsg%2F%5C%22%3ESecretary-General%20Ant%C3%B3nio%20Guterres%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%99%20concern%20that%20such%20an%20operation%20at%20present%20time%20would%20be%20potentially%20disastrous%20for%20innocent%20civilians.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20are%20more%20than%20a%20million%20people%20crammed%20in%20Rafah.%20It%E2%80%99s%20not%20intended%20for%20a%20million%20people%20in%20shelters%2C%20in%20random%20sort%20of%20plastic%20sheeted%20constructions.%20Health%20conditions%20are%20very%20worrisome%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20told%20correspondents%20in%20Brussels%20after%20briefing%20European%20Union%20foreign%20ministers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20also%20voiced%20deep%20concern%20over%20getting%20aid%20into%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%20and%20distributing%20it%20to%20those%20in%20need.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20to%20acknowledge%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20security%20conditions%2C%20separate%20from%20military%20operations%2C%20due%20to%20what%20is%20called%20self-distribution%20by%20desperate%20civilians%2C%20but%20also%20looting%20and%20criminalisation%2C%20is%20hampering%20efforts%20by%20the%20humanitarian%20community%E2%80%A6to%20deliver%20assistance%20to%20the%20people%20that%20actually%20need%20it%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMore%20needs%20to%20be%20done%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlso%20on%20Monday%2C%20UN%20Special%20Coordinator%20for%20the%20Middle%20East%20Peace%20Process%2C%20Tor%20Wennesland%2C%20visited%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%2C%20where%20he%20met%20with%20internally%20displaced%20families.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20met%20with%20NGO%20and%20UN%20personnel%20the%20see%20the%20challenges%20they%20face%20first%20hand%2C%20including%20the%20breakdown%20of%20law%20and%20order%20which%20is%20impacting%20the%20distribution%20of%20humanitarian%20supplies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20clear%20that%20more%20needs%20to%20be%20done%2C%E2%80%9D%20UN%20Spokesperson%20Stephane%20Dujarric%20told%20correspondents%20in%20New%20York%20at%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.un.org%2Fsg%2Fen%2Fcontent%2Fossg%2Fnoon-briefing-highlight%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eregular%20press%20briefing%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20UN%20needs%20the%20tools%20to%20deliver%20on%20the%20ground%2C%20including%20the%20need%20for%20Israel%20to%20allow%20entry%20of%20items%20critical%20to%20UN%20operations%20and%20to%20improve%20deconfliction%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EContinued%20hostilities%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIntense%20Israeli%20bombardment%20from%20air%2C%20land%20and%20sea%20continues%20across%20much%20of%20the%20war-torn%20enclave%2C%20according%20to%20the%20UN%20Office%20for%20the%20Coordination%20of%20Humanitarian%20Affairs%20(%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unocha.org%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOCHA%3C%2Fa%3E)%2C%20resulting%20in%20further%20civilian%20casualties%2C%20displacement%2C%20and%20destruction%20of%20civilian%20infrastructure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWidespread%20ground%20operations%20and%20heavy%20fighting%20between%20Israeli%20forces%20and%20Palestinian%20armed%20groups%20also%20continue%20to%20be%20reported%2C%20especially%20in%20Khan%20Younis%20and%20Deir%20al%20Balah%2C%20OCHA%20said%20in%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ochaopt.org%2Fcontent%2Fhostilities-gaza-strip-and-israel-flash-update-121%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eflash%20update%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0on%20Monday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBetween%2017%20and%2019%20February%2C%20dozens%20of%20rockets%20were%20also%20reportedly%20fired%20by%20armed%20Palestinians%20toward%20Israel%2C%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENasser%20hospital%20evacuations%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurthermore%2C%20the%20Israeli%20military%20operation%20in%20the%20Nasser%20Hospital%20complex%20in%20Khan%20Younis%20have%20continued%2C%20OCHA%20said%2C%20noting%20that%20on%20Sunday%2C%20the%20UN%20and%20the%20Palestine%20Red%20Crescent%20Society%20evacuated%2014%20patients.%20Negotiations%20are%20ongoing%20for%20the%20evacuation%20of%20the%20remaining%20patients.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20UN%20World%20Health%20Organization%20(%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.who.int%2Fen%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWHO%3C%2Fa%3E)%2C%20over%20180%20patients%20and%2015%20doctors%20and%20nurses%20remain%20inside%20the%20hospital.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20hospital%20is%20still%20experiencing%20an%20acute%20shortage%20of%20food%2C%20basic%20medical%20supplies%2C%20and%20oxygen.%20There%20is%20no%20tap%20water%20and%20no%20electricity%2C%20except%20a%20backup%20generator%20maintaining%20some%20lifesaving%20machines%2C%E2%80%9D%20WHO%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Steep%20rise%E2%80%99%20in%20child%20malnutrition%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUN%20agencies%20on%20Monday%20warned%20of%20a%20steep%20rise%20in%20malnutrition%20among%20children%20and%20pregnant%20and%20breastfeeding%20women%2C%20posing%20grave%20threat%20to%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20situation%20is%20especially%20serious%20in%20north%20Gaza%2C%20which%20has%20been%20almost%20completely%20cut%20off%20from%20aid%20for%20weeks%2C%20and%20where%20one%20in%20six%20children%20under%20the%20age%20of%20two%20is%20acutely%20malnourished.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20situation%20is%20not%20much%20better%20in%20southern%20Gaza%20Strip%2C%20the%20UN%20Children%E2%80%99s%20Fund%20(%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unicef.org%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUNICEF%3C%2Fa%3E)%2C%20WHO%20and%20the%20World%20Food%20Programme%20(WFP)%2C%20said%20in%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unicef.org%2Fpress-releases%2Fchildrens-lives-threatened-rising-malnutrition-gaza-strip%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enew%20report%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Rafah%2C%20where%20aid%20has%20been%20more%20available%2C%205%25%20of%20children%20under%20two%20are%20acutely%20malnourished.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20clear%20evidence%20that%20access%20to%20humanitarian%20aid%20is%20needed%20and%20can%20help%20prevent%20the%20worst%20outcomes%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20agencies%20said%2C%20reiterating%20the%20call%20to%20protect%20Rafah%20from%20the%20threat%20of%20intensified%20military%20operations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWest%20Bank%20violence%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOCHA%20also%20reported%20further%20violent%20incidents%20in%20the%20West%20Bank%20over%20the%20weekend%2C%20claiming%20both%20Israeli%20and%20Palestinian%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%2016%20February%2C%20two%20Israeli%20men%20were%20shot%20and%20killed%20in%20southern%20Israel%2C%20and%20four%20others%20including%20a%20child%20were%20injured%2C%20by%20a%20Palestinian%20man%20from%20Shu%E2%80%99fat%20refugee%20camp%20in%20East%20Jerusalem.%20The%20Palestinian%20man%20was%20then%20shot%20and%20killed%20by%20an%20armed%20Israeli%20civilian.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Sunday%2C%20Israeli%20forces%20killed%20two%20Palestinian%20men%20in%20Tulkarm%20Refugee%20camp%2C%20during%20an%20exchange%20of%20fire%20with%20a%20Palestinian%20man%20whose%20body%20was%20later%20withheld%20by%20Israeli%20forces%20from%20being%20handed%20over.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20fatality%20was%20an%20unarmed%20Palestinian%20who%20was%20reportedly%20killed%20by%20an%20Israeli%20army%20sniper%20while%20standing%20on%20the%20rooftop%20of%20his%20house%2C%20OCHA%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBetween%20October%207%2C%202023%20and%20February%2018%2C%20393%20Palestinians%20have%20been%20killed%2C%20including%20100%20children%2C%20and%204%2C511%20Palestinians%2C%20including%20699%20children%2C%20have%20been%20injured%20in%20conflict-related%20incidents%20across%20the%20West%20Bank%2C%20including%20East%20Jerusalem%2C%20and%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20same%20period%2C%2012%20Israelis%2C%20including%20four%20members%20of%20Israeli%20forces%2C%20were%20killed%20and%2080%20injured%20in%20conflict-related%20incidents%20in%20the%20same%20areas%2C%20according%20to%20OCHA.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWorld%20Court%20asked%20for%20legal%20opinion%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20at%20the%20Peace%20Palace%20in%20The%20Hague%2C%20the%20International%20Court%20of%20Justice%20(%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.icj-cij.org%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EICJ%3C%2Fa%3E)%20is%20holding%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.icj-cij.org%2Fnode%2F203551%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehearing%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0concerning%20an%20advisory%20opinion%20on%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdocuments.un.org%2Fdoc%2Fundoc%2Fgen%2Fn23%2F004%2F68%2Fpdf%2Fn2300468.pdf%3Ftoken%3Dd0pFjUBDEHpx8llwLn%26fe%3Dtrue%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELegal%20Consequences%20arising%20from%20the%20Policies%20and%20Practices%20of%20Israel%20in%20the%20Occupied%20Palestinian%20Territory%2C%20including%20East%20Jerusalem%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20advisory%2C%20non-binding%2C%20opinion%20on%20the%20occupation%20was%20requested%20by%20the%20General%20Assembly%20in%20December%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20hearings%20will%20be%20held%20from%2019%20to%2026%20February%2C%20with%20over%2050%20countries%2C%20groups%20and%20the%20State%20of%20Palestine%20scheduled%20to%20speak.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20story%20was%20originally%20published%20on%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.un.org%2Fen%2Fstory%2F2024%2F02%2F1146672%5C%22%3EUN%20News%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708428762000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F20163806%2Fimage1170x530croppe.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fisraeli-advance-on-rafah-would-have-dire-humanitarian-consequences-senior-gaza-official%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22'There%20are%20more%20than%20a%20million%20people%20crammed%20in%20Rafah.%20It's%20not%20intended%20for%20a%20million%20people%20in%20shelters%2C%20in%20random%20sort%20of%20plastic%20sheeted%20constructions.%20Health%20conditions%20are%20very%20worrisome%2C'%20said%20UN%20Senior%20Humanitarian%20Coordinator%20for%20Gaza%20Sigrid%20Kaag.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fisraeli-advance-on-rafah-would-have-dire-humanitarian-consequences-senior-gaza-official%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80%9CBack%20Door%20Linkage%20Between%20Party%20and%20Donors%20Was%20Possible%E2%80%9D%3A%20Activist%20Lokesh%20Batra%20on%20Electoral%20Bonds%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F20152920%2FBatra-Thumb-2.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20a%20landmark%20judgement%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20unanimously%20ruled%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%20unconstitutional%20on%20February%2015.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EChief%20Justice%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%2C%20leading%20a%20five-judge%20bench%2C%20emphasised%20the%20significance%20of%20transparency%20in%20political%20funding%2C%20rejecting%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20stance%20against%20disclosing%20such%20information.%20The%20ruling%20not%20only%20invalidated%20electoral%20bonds%20but%20also%20struck%20down%20related%20amendments%20to%20key%20laws.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAt%20the%20forefront%20of%20challenging%20the%20electoral%20bond%20scheme%20stands%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Flokesh-batra-electoral-bonds-scheme-rti%5C%22%3ECommodore%20Lokesh%20Batra%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%2076-year-old%20war%20veteran%20turned%20transparency%20activist.%20His%20relentless%20pursuit%20through%20the%20Right%20to%20Information%20(RTI)%20Act%20has%20exposed%20the%20opacity%20surrounding%20political%20funding%2C%20despite%20facing%20threats%20and%20intimidation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBatra%E2%80%99s%20scrutiny%20of%20the%20electoral%20bond%20scheme%2C%20initiated%20in%202017%2C%20led%20to%20over%2080%20RTI%20requests%20and%20a%20major%20expose%20in%202019%2C%20revealing%20the%20scheme%E2%80%99s%20flaws%20and%20the%20lack%20of%20accountability%20in%20political%20funding.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20spoke%20with%20Commodore%20Batra%20after%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20verdict.%20Watch%20the%20interview.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FnKezZOzM