%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Started%20by%20Anushka%20Jain%2C%20%E2%80%98Share%20At%20Door%20Step%E2%80%99%20is%20a%20social%20venture%20that%20simplifies%20the%20donation%20process.%20It%20collects%20clothes%2C%20toys%2C%20books%20and%20more%20from%20your%20doorstep%2C%20using%20AI%20to%20connect%20with%20NGOs%20throughout%20India.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Krystelle%20Dsouza%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F341906%2Fwhere-to-donate-clothes-books-toys-anushka-jain-share-at-door-step-ngos-artificial-intelligence%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20One%20Initiative%20is%20Taking%20Paediatric%20Cancer%20Care%20To%20The%20Doorsteps%20of%202500%20Kids%20in%20Rural%20India%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20is%20sponsored%20by%20The%20Hans%20Foundation%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChildhood%20cancers%20are%20a%20rising%20problem%20globally.%20The%20WHO%20states%20that%20over%20four%20lakh%20children%20develop%20cancer%20each%20year%2C%20with%20India%20accounting%20for%2050%2C000%20of%20these%20cases.%20While%20survival%20rates%20are%20high%20in%20high-income%20countries%2C%20India%20still%20faces%20the%20problems%20of%20lack%20of%20diagnosis%2C%20delayed%20diagnosis%2C%20access%20to%20care%2C%20and%20continuation%20of%20treatment.%20An%20ICMR%20(Indian%20Council%20of%20Medical%20Research)%20paper%20states%20that%20there%20is%20a%20need%20for%20specific%20policy%20work%20to%20bring%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F333669%2Fbasic-health-tests-we-should-do-regularly-heart-lungs-kidneys-cancer-detection-inspiring-story%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20childhood%20cancer%3C%2Fa%3E%20under%20control%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20an%20ICMR-NCDIR%20(National%20Centre%20for%20Disease%20Informatics%20and%20Research)%20study%20found%20that%20a%20dedicated%20paediatric%20oncology%20department%20was%20available%20in%2041.6%25%20of%20government%20hospitals.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETake%2C%20for%20instance%2C%2010-year-old%20Saksham%20(name%20changed).%20Residing%20in%20Timbi%20village%20of%20Himachal%20Pradesh%2C%20the%20playful%20child%20started%20experiencing%20unexplained%20fatigue%2C%20frequent%20infections%2C%20and%20fever%20in%202022.%20His%20father%2C%20Ramesh%20(name%20changed)%2C%20a%20farmer%2C%20consulted%20local%20doctors%20(for%20which%20he%20had%20to%20travel%2020%20km)%2C%20but%20none%20of%20the%20medications%20they%20gave%20worked%20on%20the%20child.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESaksham%20was%20then%20taken%20almost%2090%20km%20away%2C%20to%20%E2%80%98The%20Himalayan%20Hospital%E2%80%99%20in%20Dehradun%2C%20where%20blood%20tests%20revealed%20that%20he%20had%20Acute%20Lymphoblastic%20Leukaemia%20(ALL)%2C%20a%20type%20of%20blood%20cancer.%20Father%20to%20six%20children%2C%20with%20barely%20any%20income%2C%20Ramesh%20had%20already%20spent%20about%20Rs%2050%2C000%20for%20his%20travels%20and%20different%20treatments.%20The%20treatment%20for%20ALL%2C%20doctors%20estimated%2C%20would%20be%20about%20Rs%208%20lakhs.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20had%20lost%20all%20hope.%20My%20income%20was%20just%20enough%20to%20feed%20my%20family.%20I%20didn%E2%80%99t%20know%20what%20to%20do%20and%20how%20to%20save%20my%20child%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Ramesh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20doctor%20then%20informed%20Ramesh%20about%20The%20Hans%20Foundation%E2%80%99s%20Hans%20Bal%20Aarogya%20Karyakram%2C%20which%20supports%20cancer%20treatment%20and%20bone%20marrow%20transplants.%20Working%20with%20the%20hospital%20and%20the%20family%2C%20the%20programme%20has%20covered%20the%20cost%20of%20chemotherapy%2C%20bone%20marrow%20transplant%2C%20blood%20transfusions%20and%20other%20medical%20expenses%20for%20Saksham%2C%20who%20is%20now%20on%20the%20road%20to%20recovery.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Hans%20Bal%20Aarogya%20Karyakram%2C%20run%20in%20collaboration%20with%20the%20Uttarakhand%20government%2C%20is%20bridging%20the%20gap%20of%20financial%20access%20for%20children%20who%20can%E2%80%99t%20afford%20treatment%20for%20critical%20diseases%20like%20cancer.%20So%20far%2C%20over%202%2C500%20children%20have%20benefited%20from%20this%20initiative%20and%20have%20received%20life-saving%20treatments.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EHelping%20parents%20access%20quality%20cancer%20care%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20853px)%20100vw%2C%20853px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2FHans1-1707980361.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22853%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Hans%20Bal%20Aarogya%20Karyakram%2C%20in%20partnership%20with%20the%20Uttarakhand%20government%2C%20is%20closing%20the%20financial%20gap%20for%20children%20unable%20to%20afford%20treatment%20for%20serious%20illnesses%20such%20as%20cancer.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2FHans1-1707980361.jpg%20853w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2FHans1-1707980361-200x300.jpg%20200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2FHans1-1707980361-500x750.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2FHans1-1707980361-768x1152.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2FHans1-1707980361-150x225.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-341893%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20Hans%20Bal%20Aarogya%20Karyakram%2C%20in%20partnership%20with%20the%20Uttarakhand%20Government%2C%20is%20closing%20the%20financial%20gap%20for%20children%20unable%20to%20afford%20treatment%20for%20serious%20illnesses%2C%20such%20as%20cancer.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEstablished%20in%202017%20in%20close%20partnership%20with%20the%20state%20government%2C%20the%20programme%20provides%20free%20treatment%20to%20children%20aged%200-18%20years%20who%20are%20suffering%20from%20critical%20diseases%20or%20conditions%2C%20complementing%20the%20Rashtriya%20Bal%20Swasthya%20Karyakram%20(RBSK)%20and%20subsequently%2C%20Ayushman%20Bharat%20schemes%20by%20supporting%20treatment%20for%20conditions%20outside%20the%20schemes%E2%80%99%20purview%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20District%20Early%20Intervention%20Centers%20(DEICs)%2C%20established%20under%20the%20RBSK%2C%20identify%20infants%20and%20children%20with%20developmental%20delays%2C%20disabilities%20and%20diseases.%20Once%20identified%2C%20these%20children%20are%20referred%20to%20two%20empanelled%20medical%20colleges%2C%20namely%20The%20Himalayan%20Hospital%20(Swami%20Ram%20Himalayan%20University)%20and%20Shri%20Mahant%20Indresh%20Hospital.%20The%20Hans%20Foundation%20has%20partnered%20with%20these%20two%20colleges%20and%20reimburses%20the%20treatment%20expenses%20for%20diseases%20like%20cancer.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20programme%20is%20broadly%20designed%2C%2090%20percent%20of%20the%20patients%20who%20need%20support%20are%20cancer%20patients%2C%20as%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F322528%2Futtar-pradesh-cancer-survivor-sandeep-kumar-runs-digiswasthya-free-medical-teleconsultation%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecancer%20treatments%3C%2Fa%3E%20require%20a%20lot%20of%20time%20and%20money.%20The%20average%20cost%20of%20treating%20common%20cancers%20in%20children%20like%20ALL%20and%20Acute%20Myeloid%20Leukaemia%20(AML)%20can%20easily%20range%20from%20Rs%205-15%20lakhs%20or%20even%20more%2C%20depending%20on%20the%20complexity%20of%20the%20disease%20at%20the%20time%20of%20diagnosis.%20Most%20of%20the%20children%20who%20come%20in%20for%20treatment%20are%20either%20infants%2C%20or%20between%20the%20age%20group%20of%205-8.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECommon%20cancers%20in%20children%20are%20different%20from%20those%20seen%20in%20adults.%20Dr%20BP%20Kalra%2C%20Professor%20of%20Pediatrics%2C%20Department%20of%20Pediatrics%2C%20Himalayan%20Institute%20of%20Medical%20Sciences%2C%20Dehradun%20states%20that%20leukaemias%20(cancer%20of%20blood-forming%20tissues)%2C%20lymphomas%20(cancer%20of%20the%20lymphatic%20system)%20are%20the%20most%20common%2C%20followed%20by%20brain%20and%20bone%20cancer%20and%20tumours%20like%20the%20Wilms%20Tumour%20(renal%20cancer).%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20see%20that%20most%20commonly%2C%20children%20get%20cancer%20in%20the%20first%20or%20second%20year%20of%20life%2C%20or%20in%20the%205-10%20age%20group.%20In%20the%20school-going%20age%20group%2C%20leukaemias%20and%20lymphomas%20are%20most%20common.%20The%20outcome%20is%20generally%20good%20in%20this%20age%20group%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Dr%20Kalra.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Himalayan%20Institute%20caters%20to%20children%20from%20across%20Uttarakhand%2C%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20and%20sometimes%20Punjab%2C%20Haryana%2C%20Himachal%20Pradesh%20and%20more.%C2%A0%20The%20reason%2C%20the%20doctor%20adds%2C%20is%20because%20of%20lack%20of%20facilities%20for%20treatment%2C%20which%20makes%20parents%20and%20children%20travel%20far%20and%20wide%20for%20basic%20access.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20is%20needed%20for%20good%20outcomes%2C%20according%20to%20Dr%20Kalra%2C%20is%20an%20early%2C%20prompt%2C%20correct%20diagnosis%20which%20should%20be%20followed%20by%20effective%2C%20evidence-based%20therapy%20after%20which%20supportive%20care%20is%20paramount.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EHelping%202%2C500%20children%20get%20cancer%20treatment%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2FH